What is mysticism? Mysticism is the acceptance of allegations without evidence
or proof, either apart from or <em>against</em> the evidence of one&#x2019;s senses and one&#x2019;s
reason. Mysticism is the claim to some non-sensory, non-rational,
non-definable, non-identifiable means of knowledge, such as &#x201C;instinct,&#x201D;
&#x201C;intuition,&#x201D; &#x201C;revelation,&#x201D; or any form of &#x201C;just knowing.&#x201D;
